[{"location":"Visualize/ShowGof/#Gof","page":"Gof","title":"Gof","text":"Render a compact multiline block of GoF metrics at a chosen position on an axis. Metrics are computed internally via gof and can be filtered via the metrics keyword.","category":"section"},{"location":"Visualize/ShowGof/#Examples","page":"Gof","title":"Examples","text":"using Junimo # hide\nusing CairoMakie # hide\n\nCairoMakie.activate!() # hide\n\nyobs = [1, 2, 3, 4, 5]\nysim = [1, 2, 3, 4, 6]\n\n\nfig = Figure(; size=(700, 350))\n\nax = Axis(\n  fig[1, 1], titlefont = :regular,\n  xlabel = \"Yobs (-)\", ylabel = \"Ysim (-)\"\n)\nscatter!(ax, yobs, ysim; markersize=10, color=:lightblue)\nlines!(ax, [0, 6], [0, 6]; color=:red, linestyle=:dash, linewidth=2)\nshow_gof!(\n  ax, 5.3, 0.1,\n  yobs, ysim;\n  metrics = [\"R2\", \"RMSE\"],\n  n=2,\n  align=(:right, :bottom),\n  color=:black\n)\nfig","category":"section"},{"location":"Visualize/ShowGof/#APIs","page":"Gof","title":"APIs","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"Visualize/ShowGof/#Junimo.show_gof!","page":"Gof","title":"Junimo.show_gof!","text":"show_gof!(ax, x, y, obs, sim; metrics=nothing, n=nothing, align=(:right, :bottom), color=:black)\n\nRender GoF metrics at a given position on an existing axis. The metrics are computed internally via gof(obs, sim) and then formatted as multiline text.\n\nArguments\n\nax: Makie axis to draw on\nx, y: Text position coordinates\nobs, sim: Observed and simulated values (scalars or sequences)\n\nKeywords\n\nmetrics: List of metric keys to display (e.g. [\"R2\", \"NSE\"]). If nothing, defaults to [\"R2\", \"NSE\", \"KGE\", \"RMSE\", \"bias\"].\nn: Decimal digits to round to; forwarded to gof(...; n_small=n).\nalign: Text alignment tuple passed to text!.\ncolor: Text color passed to text!.\n\nNotes\n\nUnknown metric keys are shown as NaN.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"Statistics/Gof/#Gof","page":"Gof","title":"Gof","text":"Compute a composite set of goodness-of-fit metrics between observed and simulated values. Missing values are filtered pairwise, and optional rounding is supported via n_small.","category":"section"},{"location":"Statistics/Gof/#Examples","page":"Gof","title":"Examples","text":"using Junimo # hide\n\nyobs = [1, 2, 3, 4, 5]\nysim = [1, 2, 3, 4, 6]\n\ngof(yobs, ysim)\n\nusing Junimo # hide\n\ngof(1, 1)\n\nusing Junimo # hide\n\nyobs = [1, missing, 3, 4, 5]\nysim = [1, 2, missing, 4, 6]\n\ngof(yobs, ysim; n_small=3)","category":"section"},{"location":"Statistics/Gof/#APIs","page":"Gof","title":"APIs","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"Statistics/Gof/#Junimo.gof","page":"Gof","title":"Junimo.gof","text":"gof(obs, sim; n_small=nothing)\n\nComposite goodness-of-fit (GoF) metrics comparing simulated sim with observed obs. Missing values are removed pairwise: iterate zip(obs, sim) and keep only non-missing pairs.\n\nReturns\n\nKGE, NSE, R, R2\nRMSE, MAE, bias, bias_perc\nn\n\nArguments\n\nobs, sim: Numeric sequences or scalars, may include missing\nn_small: Optional number of decimal digits to round to; nothing keeps full precision\n\nFormulae\n\nRMSE = sqrtfrac1n sum (s_i - o_i)^2\nMAE = frac1n sum s_i - o_i\nbias = bars - baro\nbias_perc = 100 cdot bias  baro\nNSE = 1 - fracsum (s_i - o_i)^2sum (o_i - baro)^2\nKGE = 1 - sqrt(r-1)^2 + (alpha-1)^2 + (beta-1)^2 where r = cor(o s), alpha = sigma_s  sigma_o, beta = barsbaro\n\nStability and edge cases\n\nWhen n <= 2, KGE/NSE/R/R2 return NaN\nWhen baro = 0 or sigma_o = 0, the related ratio terms return NaN\n\nReferences\n\nNash, J. E., & Sutcliffe, J. V. (1970). River flow forecasting through conceptual models. Journal of Hydrology, 10(3), 282-290. doi:10.1016/0022-1694(70)90255-6\nGupta, H. V., Kling, H., Yilmaz, K. K., & Martinez, G. F. (2009). Decomposition of the mean squared error and NSE: Toward improved diagnostic evaluation. Water Resources Research, 45, W09417. doi:10.1029/2009WR007200\nWillmott, C. J., & Matsuura, K. (2005). Advantages of the mean absolute error (MAE). Climate Research, 30, 79-82. doi:10.3354/cr030079\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"Utils/Print/#Print","page":"Print","title":"Print","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"Utils/Print/#Examples","page":"Print","title":"Examples","text":"using Junimo # hide\n\nred(\"Red text\")\ngreen(\"Green text\")\nblue(\"Blue text\")\npurple(\"Purple text\")\n\n@red \"Red text (macro)\"\n@green \"Green text (macro)\"\n@blue \"Blue text (macro)\"\n@purple \"Purple text (macro)\"","category":"section"},{"location":"Utils/Print/#APIs","page":"Print","title":"APIs","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"Utils/Print/#Junimo.cprint","page":"Print","title":"Junimo.cprint","text":"cprint(text, code)\ncprint(io, text, code)\n\nPrint text to standard output using the specified ANSI color code.\n\nThis is a low-level utility function for customized terminal output.\n\nArguments\n\ntext: The string to print.\ncode: The integer ANSI color code (e.g., 31 for red, 32 for green).\nio: Optional IO stream to write to.\n\nExamples\n\ncprint(\"System initialized\", 33) # Prints yellow text\ncprint(stderr, \"Warning\", 33)\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"Utils/Print/#Junimo.red","page":"Print","title":"Junimo.red","text":"red(text)\nred(io, text)\n\nPrint a line of text in Red (ANSI 31).\n\nTypically used for errors, warnings, or to indicate \"Bad Luck\" (the Red Skull from the Fortune Teller).\n\nExamples\n\nred(\"Error: Data mismatch detected!\")\nred(stderr, \"Error: Data mismatch detected!\")\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"Utils/Print/#Junimo.green","page":"Print","title":"Junimo.green","text":"green(text)\ngreen(io, text)\n\nPrint a line of text in Green (ANSI 32).\n\nThis is the color of the Junimos. Use this to indicate success, completed tasks, or stable model conditions.\n\nExamples\n\ngreen(\"Processing complete. Junimos are happy.\")\ngreen(stderr, \"Processing complete. Junimos are happy.\")\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"Utils/Print/#Junimo.blue","page":"Print","title":"Junimo.blue","text":"blue(text)\nblue(io, text)\n\nPrint a line of text in Blue (ANSI 34).\n\nUse this for general information, hydrological data outputs, or water-related metrics.\n\nExamples\n\nblue(\"Lake level stabilized.\")\nblue(stderr, \"Hydrology data missing.\")\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"Utils/Print/#Junimo.purple","page":"Print","title":"Junimo.purple","text":"purple(text)\npurple(io, text)\n\nPrint a line of text in Purple (ANSI 35).\n\nThis is the color of Iridium and Stardrops. Use this for high-priority messages, significant results, or \"Great Luck\" days.\n\nExamples\n\npurple(\"Optimization finished! Results are Iridium quality.\")\npurple(stderr, \"Optimization finished! Results are Iridium quality.\")\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"Utils/Print/#Junimo.@red","page":"Print","title":"Junimo.@red","text":"@red text\n@red io text\n\nPrint a line of text in Red (ANSI 31).\n\nThis macro expands to red(text) or red(io, text).\n\nExamples\n\n@red \"Error: Data mismatch detected!\"\n@red stderr \"Error: Data mismatch detected!\"\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"macro"},{"location":"Utils/Print/#Junimo.@green","page":"Print","title":"Junimo.@green","text":"@green text\n@green io text\n\nPrint a line of text in Green (ANSI 32).\n\nThis macro expands to green(text) or green(io, text).\n\nExamples\n\n@green \"Processing complete. Junimos are happy.\"\n@green stderr \"Processing complete. Junimos are happy.\"\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"macro"},{"location":"Utils/Print/#Junimo.@blue","page":"Print","title":"Junimo.@blue","text":"@blue text\n@blue io text\n\nPrint a line of text in Blue (ANSI 34).\n\nThis macro expands to blue(text) or blue(io, text).\n\nExamples\n\n@blue \"Lake level stabilized.\"\n@blue stderr \"Hydrology data missing.\"\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"macro"},{"location":"Utils/Print/#Junimo.@purple","page":"Print","title":"Junimo.@purple","text":"@purple text\n@purple io text\n\nPrint a line of text in Purple (ANSI 35).\n\nThis macro expands to purple(text) or purple(io, text).\n\nExamples\n\n@purple \"Optimization finished! Results are Iridium quality.\"\n@purple stderr \"Optimization finished! Results are Iridium quality.\"\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"macro"},{"location":"#Junimo.jl","page":"Junimo.jl","title":"Junimo.jl","text":"(Image: Tests) (Image: Documentation)\n\nJunimo.jl is a personal Julia utility library, aimed at automating and streamlining day-to-day workflows.","category":"section"},{"location":"#Table-of-Contents","page":"Junimo.jl","title":"Table of Contents","text":"Junimo.jl\nTable of Contents\nOverview\nAuthor\nFunction Categories\nInstallation\nQuick Start\nTesting\nDocumentation\nContributing\nLicense","category":"section"},{"location":"#Overview","page":"Junimo.jl","title":"Overview","text":"Junimo.jl gathers practical helpers and conventions into a single package. It favors small, composable utilities that can be reused across projects and scripts.","category":"section"},{"location":"#Author","page":"Junimo.jl","title":"Author","text":"YuxuanXie","category":"section"},{"location":"#Function-Categories","page":"Junimo.jl","title":"Function Categories","text":"Utils: colored console output helpers (cprint, red, green, blue, purple and macros)\nStatistics: goodness-of-fit metrics (gof)\nVisualize: GoF annotation helpers for Makie (show_gof!)","category":"section"},{"location":"#Installation","page":"Junimo.jl","title":"Installation","text":"pkg> add https://github.com/cug-xyx/Junimo.jl","category":"section"},{"location":"#Quick-Start","page":"Junimo.jl","title":"Quick Start","text":"using Junimo","category":"section"},{"location":"#Testing","page":"Junimo.jl","title":"Testing","text":"julia --project -e \"using Pkg; Pkg.test()\"","category":"section"},{"location":"#Documentation","page":"Junimo.jl","title":"Documentation","text":"Documentation site: https://cug-xyx.github.io/Junimo.jl/index.html","category":"section"},{"location":"#Contributing","page":"Junimo.jl","title":"Contributing","text":"Contributions are welcome. Please open an issue to discuss ideas before submitting a PR.","category":"section"},{"location":"#License","page":"Junimo.jl","title":"License","text":"GPL-3.0-only","category":"section"}]
